definitions.definition: Mechanical routine ; a fixed , habitual , repetitive , or mechanical course of procedure.
examples: The pastoral scenes from those commercials don’t bear too much resemblance to the rote of daily life on a farm.
He could perform by rote any of his roles in Shakespeare.

main_definition: Mechanical routine ; a fixed , habitual , repetitive , or mechanical course of procedure.

definitions.definition: ( rare ) The roar of the surf ; the sound of waves breaking on the shore. [from c. 1600]

definitions.definition: A kind of guitar , the notes of which were produced by a small wheel or wheel-like arrangement; an instrument similar to the hurdy-gurdy .
